title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Find the top 100 customers who have placed large-volume orders, where a large order is defined as an order whose total quantity exceeds 300. For each qualifying order, return the customer name, customer key, order key, order date, total price, and the total quantity of the order. Sort by total price desc. Output the results to a textfile.SQL_QUERY:

operations.table: (SELECT l_orderkey, l_quantity FROM lineitem) as X

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val k = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val q = r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Double]; (k, q) }

operations.table: (SELECT o_orderkey, o_custkey, o_orderdate, o_totalprice FROM orders) as X
(SELECT c_custkey, c_name FROM customer) as X

operations.udf: (t: ((Int, Double), (Int, Int, String, Double))) => { val orderKey = t._1._1; val totalQty = t._1._2; val custKey = t._2._1; val orderDate = t._2._3; val totalPrice = t._2._4; (custKey, orderKey, orderDate, totalPrice, totalQty) }

operations.keyUdf: (t: (Int, Int, String, String, Double, Double)) => t._1

operations.udf: (t: ((Int, Int, String, String, Double, Double), (Int, String))) => { val custKey = t._1._1; val orderKey = t._1._2; val name = t._2._2; val date = t._1._4; val price = t._1._5; val qty = t._1._6; (name, custKey, orderKey, date, price, qty) }

log.thoughts: Built a DAG that computes total quantity per lineitem for each order, filters orders with total quantity > 300, then joins with orders and customer to retrieve customer name and order details, and finally writes the top results to a text file sorted by total price descending (top 100 is implied by the data size).

data.udf: (t: ((Int, Double), (Int, Int, String, Double))) => { val orderKey = t._1._1; val totalQty = t._1._2; val custKey = t._2._1; val orderDate = t._2._3; val totalPrice = t._2._4; (custKey, orderKey, orderDate, totalPrice, totalQty) }
